non_rollback,suspend)\\n     *\\n     * @return the boolean\\n     */\\n    boolean useTCCFence() default false;\\n\\n    /**\\n     * commit method's args\\n     *\\n     * @return the Class[]\\n     */\\n    Class<?>[] commitArgsClasses() default {BusinessActionContext.class};\\n\\n    /**\\n     * rollback method's args\\n     *\\n     * @return the Class[]\\n     */\\n    Class<?>[] rollbackArgsClasses() default {BusinessActionContext.class};\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777941168101}]}\n1433:[tool-call] delta {\"command\":\"git status --short\"}\n1434:[tool-call] end id=call_C4Kbq2fHDi3kVBs0laXKWVOy|fc_0ec98295888b28f90169f93abff5fc8190828802e453f9cba8 name=bash args={\"command\": \"git status --short\"}\n1435:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Checking git worktree status**\\n\\nI’m slightly puzzled by the lack of differences. Maybe checking the git worktree status could give me more insight into what's happening here. It seems like a reasonable next step to see if that helps clarify things. By looking at the worktree status, I might discover more about the current situation or any uncommitted changes that I might have overlooked. Let's see where this leads!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0ec98295888b28f90169f93abe82ec81909b00798ebaf153d8\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-Tq_-W5xn0e8zdE9FX4pV9JjFMYP2Jm9FJtHa-M8zhoWil8DD7Upnj5xonOluPO-_eussJbyAiBxNqGPEAAHbzy3wpd5BGbaK-1_EgDM7woUllqBWU9YmJYCZR2hTjB8h8WurtdW8Ql5vzjSL1_lTPqn12-rMCof6-62iOHsvMqbxsWmersjgjIS07VtBxLXjRm37WLjbNZfcADzC99LxuhqDnlEWwDgcSZYMe333zZJNEuxmlC5qqKoZtHwKtK8v19TQW-yRaD4FonfSzvd97dB0EfJNQFFIU_mAE7usYEYHnmbGz2-zoMLi5krjLQLw_H2JhBy4qMLEdg1Rz7gPXy77h5HcKPO7tH5iybBITjMdhVti8hFkzlwTuVOt0dCOxyrtNb8X73-wVLQ5bDvtmMPf4e1Vidr44nU2dMsNY_yioAXuVIbn4X7uVGazHr0FHumcy2ZTYSvWLhWc1BVqRV2mJOWdQ2qZCQ5FJveqzycRIjzuP31ngJAxPiHipS-THUQdBhSQYFn1VuTcCL